ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.unodc.org/documents/gsh/pdfs/2014_GLOBAL_HOMICIDE_BOOK_web.pdf|title = Global Study on Homicide|date = 2013|accessdate = |website = www.unodc.org|publisher = United National Office of Drugs and Crime (Vienna)|last = Gibbons|first = Jonathan}}</ref> and 79% of the victims (see the chart below). The homicide rate is per year per 100,000 inhabitants.\n\n{{Rank| rows={{TRC|ignore=4|id=nations}}| header-lines=7| caption=Homicide Victims by Gender, by Country<ref name=UNDOC1>[http://www.unodc.org/gsh/en/data.html UNDOC Homicide Statistics 2013] used tables: [http://www.unodc.org/documents/gsh/data/GSH2013_Homicide_count_and_rate.xlsx Homicide counts and rates] & [http://www.unodc.org/documents/gsh/data/GSH2013_Sex_data.xlsx Percentage of male and female homicide victims] Retrieved May-31-2014</ref>}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable nowrap mw-datatable\" border=1 style=\"text-align:right;\" id=\"nations\"\n|- \n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=3 |<br><br><br><br><br><br>'''Country'''\n! colspan=\"2\" | Total\n! colspan=\"3\" | Male\n! colspan=\"3\" | Female\n! colspan=\"3\" |\n|- valign=bottom\n! scope=\"col\" |'''Homicides'''\n! scope=\"col\" |'''Homicide<br>Rate'''\n! scope=\"col\" |'''% of<br>victims<br>male'''\n! scope=\"col\" |'''Homicides'''\n! scope=\"col\" |'''Homicide<br>Rate'''\n! scope=\"col\" |'''% of<br>victims<br>female'''\n! scope=\"col\" |'''Homicides'''\n! scope=\"col\" |'''Homicide<br>Rate'''\n! scope=\"col\" |'''Year'''\n|-\n! <br> !! !! !! !! !! !! !! !! \n|-\n| align=left|{{flaglist|Afghanistan}}||1,948||6.5||87.0%||1,695||5.7||13.0%||253||0.8||2010\n|-\n| align=left|{{flaglist|Albania}}||157||5.0||83.4%||131||4.2||16.6%||26||0.8||2009\n|-\n| align=left|{{flaglist|Algeria}}||280||0.7||84.0%||235||0.6||16.0%||45||0.1||2012\n|-\n| align=left|{{flaglist|Angola}}||2,079||10.0||81.2%||1,688||8.1||18.8%||391||1.9||2010\n|-\n| align=left|{{flaglist|Anguilla}}||1||7.5||100.0%||1||7.5||0.0%||0||0.0||2010\n|-\n| align=left|{{flaglist|Antigu